Id agi .- ‘ that it was in agitation,‘ ‘ that exertions were mak- ing.’ This isa peculiar phrase: the pronoun id has no antece dent, but refers to the following clause3 being used superfluously, and always followed by ut with the subjunctive, where the pro- noun itself would be omitted in English, with the following verb in the infinitive.
